<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Floating non-replaced-block elements with auto width</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify non-replaced-block level element uses correct auto width in floated container with auto width." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                background-color: red;
                float: left;
            }
            #d2
            {
                height: 2em;
                width: 200px;
                background-color: green;
            }
            #d3
            {
                height: 2em;
                background-color: green;
            }
            #d4
            {
                height: 2em;
                background-color: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if a big green box is on the page and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2"></div>
            <div id="d3"></div>
            <div id="d4"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>